<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFFB0144600EF7A691598A97" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFFB0144600EF7A691598A97" blockId="25.[828,1436,1958,2077]" lastBlockId="26.[151,760,190,437]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB0147600EF7A690CF8C9F" bold="true" box="[828,958,1958,1981]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Comments.</emphasis>
The description of this species contains two different names. While in the abstract and the description, the name 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB01476098F7E697DE8CDF" authorityName="Medvedev &amp; Romantsov" authorityYear="2013" box="[938,1199,2022,2045]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thailandica">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB01476098F7E697DE8CDF" box="[938,1199,2022,2045]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Platyxantha thailandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was used, the colour photographs of the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFFB01476723F806971F833F" box="[1041,1134,2054,2077]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">holotype</typeStatus>
habitus and aedeagus were provided with the name 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014462ABF0BE912F8BF7" authorityName="Medvedev &amp; Romantsov" authorityYear="2013" box="[409,606,190,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hyphaenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014462ABF0BE912F8BF7" box="[409,606,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Hyphaenia tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF8014461A8F0BE91868BF7" box="[666,759,190,213]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">holotype</typeStatus>
is deposited in the collection of Pavel Romantsov (
<collectingRegion id="462391AAFFF8014461E8F0DE927B8A37" country="Russia" name="Saint Petersburg" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">St. Petersburg</collectingRegion>
) who kindly checked that it has no metasternal process and no apical spine on the metatibia. In my opinion this species belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014462A7F13E917B8A77" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1865" box="[405,522,318,341]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hyphaenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014462A7F13E917B8A77" box="[405,522,318,341]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Hyphaenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because the original description contains two names for a single taxon I fix the name 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014463EBF17E92D18AB7" authorityName="Medvedev &amp; Romantsov" authorityYear="2013" box="[217,416,382,405]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hyphaenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014463EBF17E92D18AB7" box="[217,416,382,405]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Hyphaenia tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the correct one based on the Art. 32.2.1 of the Code (
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF8014462AEF19E916A8A97" author="ICZN" bookContentInfo="306 pp." box="[412,539,414,437]" firstAuthor="ICZN" journalOrPublisher="International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" refId="ref31036" refString="ICZN 1999: International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." title="International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition" type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
